    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Porsche's Sport Utility</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William Motley letter comments on Porsche's decision to produce sport utility vehicle (Dec 17 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Sadly, Porsche felt incomplete without an S.U.V. in its fleet (Business Day, Dec. 17). But the question is not whether it will ''dilute the purity'' of the name; it is whether automakers will reduce carbon dioxide emissions. Porsche executives should talk about the environment the way they talk about the company's near-death experience in the 90's, ''with a shiver in their voices.''</p>
        <p>WILLIAM MOTLEY  Brooklyn, Dec. 17, 2002</p>
      </block>
